

To add git access:
first generate the ssh keys

Run the terminal on your VM and execute the following commands 
ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "your_email"
Press Enter to select the default path

Enter and re-enter a password (or press enter twice to have no password)
Go to Filesâ†’Home and press Ctrl+H to show the hidden files and directories (if you are in the web console. If you SSHed, read the note below for step 5-7*)
Go to .ssh directory and open the file id_rsa.pub (will open in Libre Office) Do not modify this file.
Copy the entire contents (starts with ssh-rha and ends with your email)
Login in your github account add these ssh keys in settings SSH.
Once done
you can directly access the repo using ssh and git commands
